<h1>The PDA application.</h1>
This is the component that resides on the PDA. The PDA application is an interface to a number of <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/Demo_Project/Demo_App/DataSets/">OnBoardData Classes</a>, which are derived from <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/PDAData.vb">this class</a>. <br><br>
This base class is inherited by all recordsets (eg <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/Demo_Project/Demo_App/DataSets/_ServiceCall.vb">the Service Call Recordset</a>). 
The base class exposes methods that download, process and syncronise data beteen the record set and the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/">IIS Web Service</a>. <br><br>
The <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/Demo_Project/Demo_App/App.vb">main PDA application</a> is also derived from a <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/BaseForm.vb">base class</a> that aggregates the array of <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/Demo_Project/Demo_App/DataSets/">onboad data classes</a> and encapsulates the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/q.vb">message queue</a>.